      • transformToListOrdered

        public static <L> List<LabeledVector<L>> transformToListOrdered(Queue<PointWithDistance<L>> points)
        Util method that transforms collection of PointWithDistance to array of LabeledVector. Be aware that this method uses Queue.remove() method to extract elements and the asymptotic complexity of this method depends on it (in case of PriorityQueue it will be O(log(n)), in case of LinkedList it will be O(n)).
        Type Parameters:
        L - Label type.
        Parameters:
        points - Collections of PointWithDistance.
        Returns:
        Array of LabeledVector

      • tryToAddIntoHeap

        public static <L> void tryToAddIntoHeap(Queue<PointWithDistance<L>> heap,
                                        int k,
                                        LabeledVector<L> dataPnt,
                                        double distance)
        Util method that adds data point into heap if it fits (if heap size is less than k or a distance from taget point to data point is less than a distance from target point to the most distant data point in heap).
        Type Parameters:
        L - Label type.
        Parameters:
        heap - Heap with closest points.
        k - Number of neighbours.
        dataPnt - Data point to be added.
        distance - Distance to target point.
